snippet.textDisplay:
Would love to see your reactions to Japanese Tokusatsu (Super Sentai, Kamen Rider, Ultraman, etc but I'm a Kamen Rider fan mainly so seeing that would kill me but like, in a good way). I think the blend of computer and practical effects over the years in terms of their morphing/henshin/transformation sequences would be pretty cool to look at. And the sheer craziness of what they try to accomplish. Might make for fun during the stunt reacts as well since it's lots of wire work and explosions.



I think Kamen rider Decade (2009) has some pretty good content, since its a look back at the series and also because Tsukasa Kadoya (Masahiro Inoue) is bae. Also also, the only Anti-Villain as protagonist that I can think of in recent media.


Compared to Kamen Rider Zi-Oh (2018/19) and the greatness that is the chungus TIME MAJIN mechs and baby Sogo Tokiwa (So Okuno) who is supposed to be "the strongest rider of all time", and the final rider from the Heisei era.
